Description: Wooden shabti, mummiform, with tripartite headgear, eyes and cosmetic line painted in black, along left side of figure one line of large hieratic signs identifying the owner as a woman Tetinefer born of Nynaia, along the front five vertical columns of hieratic without ligatures giving chapter 6 of the book of the Dead.
Acquisition name: Purchased through: Sir Ernest A T Wallis Budge
